	Indicate by check mark if disclosure of delinquent filers pursuant to Item&#160;405 of Regulation&#160;S-K (&#167;229.405 of this chapter) is not contained herein, and will not be contained, to the best of registrant&#8217;s knowledge, in definitive proxy or information statements incorporated by reference in Part&#160;III of this Form&#160;10-K or any amendment to this Form&#160;10-K.&#160;&#160;

	Indicate by check mark whether the registrant is a large accelerated filer, an accelerated filer, a non-accelerated filer, or a smaller reporting company. 	The statements included in this Form 10-K regarding future financial performance, results and conditions and other statements that are not historical facts, including, among others, the statements regarding competition, the Company&#8217;s intention to retain earnings for use in the Company&#8217;s business operations, the Company&#8217;s ability to continue to fund its operations and service its indebtedness, the adequacy of the Company&#8217;s accrual for tax liabilities, management&#8217;s projection of continued taxable income, and the Company&#8217;s ability to offset future income against net operating loss carryovers, constitute forward-looking statements. <TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">

<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_1_BUSINESS">
</A>
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_1_BUSINESS">
</A>
	ITEM 1. BUSINESS.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Overview and Business Organization
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ Regional Holdings, Inc. (including subsidiaries, referred to collectively in this Report as &#8220;ALJ,&#8221; the &#8220;Company&#8221; or &#8220;we&#8221;) is a holding company.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ&#8217;s primary assets as of September&#160;30, 2016, were all of the outstanding capital stock of the following companies:
</P>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#x2022;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Faneuil, Inc. (including its subsidiaries, &#8220;Faneuil&#8221;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Faneuil is a leading provider of call center services, back office operations, staffing services and toll collection services to government and regulated commercial clients across the United States, focusing on the healthcare, utility, toll and transportation industries. Faneuil is headquartered in Hampton, Virginia. ALJ acquired Faneuil effective October&#160;19, 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#x2022;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Floors-N-More, LLC, dba, Carpets N&#8217; More (&#8220;Carpets&#8221;)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Carpets is one of the largest floor covering retailers in Las Vegas, Nevada, and a provider of multiple products for the commercial, retail and home builder markets including all types of flooring, countertops, cabinets, window coverings and garage/closet organizers, with five retail locations, as well as a stone and solid surface fabrication facility. ALJ acquired Carpets effective April&#160;1, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#x2022;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Phoenix Color Corp. (including its subsidiaries, &#8220;Phoenix&#8221;).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;Phoenix is a leading manufacturer of book components, educational materials and related products producing value-added components, heavily illustrated books and specialty commercial products using a broad spectrum of materials and decorative technologies. Phoenix is headquartered in Hagerstown, Maryland. ALJ acquired Phoenix effective August&#160;9, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	With several members of senior management and our Board of Directors coming from long careers in the professional service industry, ALJ is focused on acquiring and operating exceptional customer service-based businesses.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ has organized its business and corporate structure along the following business segments: Faneuil, Carpets and Phoenix. ALJ is reported as corporate overhead.&nbsp;&nbsp; For results of operations by business segment, see &#8220;Part II, Item 7. Management&#8217;s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Faneuil
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Background
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil is a Delaware corporation with headquarters in Hampton, VA. We acquired Faneuil from Harland Clarke Holdings Corp, a wholly owned subsidiary of MacAndrews&#160;&amp; Forbes Holdings Inc., for aggregate consideration of $53.0&#160;million in 2013.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil is a nationally recognized leader in technology-enabled in-person and automated service delivery, particularly in regulated, highly complex environments.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Services
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil provides business processing solutions for an extensive client portfolio that includes both commercial and government entities across several verticals, including transportation, government services, utilities and healthcare. Utilizing advanced applications and a dedicated team of service professionals, Faneuil delivers broad outsourcing support, ranging from customer contact centers, fulfillment operations and information technology services, to manual and electronic toll collection, violation processing and medical device tracking, with the goal of building its clients&#8217; brands by providing exemplary customer service.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s core competencies include:
</P>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#x2022;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:'TIMES NEW ROMAN';FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	High-volume, multi-channel customer contact centers;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Staffing services.

</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s customer contact employees undergo intensive training and development, followed by structured monitoring and assessments before they are certified to process customer contacts. Faneuil&#8217;s customer contact employees provide service delivery through multiple communication channels, including telephone, fax, email, web chat and face-to-face interaction. Additionally, Faneuil provides multi-lingual representatives to accommodate the communication needs of non-English-speaking customers, as well as the hearing-impaired.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employees
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil had 3,425 employees as of September&#160;30, 2016 all located in the U.S. None of Faneuil&#8217;s employees are subject to any collective bargaining agreements. Faneuil considers its employee relations good.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Customers
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s client portfolio includes both government and commercial entities nationwide, including several toll authorities, state agencies, municipalities, a publicly owned utility, two health benefit exchanges, one government agency that operates the major airports serving the Washington, D.C. area, and several other public and private entities.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The percentages of Faneuil net revenues derived from its significant customers for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015 were as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:1PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;

<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:4.54%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:2PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#94;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:2PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Customer A represented 17.8% and 24.3% of ALJ&#8217;s consolidated net revenues for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;Contract 1 concluded in October 2016.&#160; In the normal course of business, the Company experiences contract turnover.&#160; The revenue reduction resulting from this contract conclusion has been replaced with a new customer.&#160;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	**

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Less than 10% of Faneuil net revenues.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Many of Faneuil&#8217;s customers are government agencies subject to contractual budgetary ceilings. State and local funding for these agencies are approved by the respective state legislature(s) each year. Depending on budgetary constraints, the contract values may be subject to change based upon ongoing legislative approval.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Competition
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s primary competitors are other large providers of toll services, such as Xerox, AEComm and TransCore, Inc., as well as contact center operators such as Maximus and Alberta Health Services. In many cases, Faneuil is smaller and has less financial and personnel resources than its competitors. If Faneuil cannot compete effectively to win new business and retain existing clients, its operating results will be negatively affected. To remain competitive, Faneuil must continuously implement new technologies and expand its portfolio of outsourced services and may have to make occasional strategic adjustments to its pricing for its services.
</P>
</EFX_BUSINESS>
<EFX_PROPERTIES>
<A NAME="FIS_PROPERTIES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Properties
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU6">
</A>
	Faneuil leases all its properties with various locations throughout the United States for customer contact centers, walk-in retail, and administration. Corporate headquarters are located in Hampton, VA. Faneuil&#8217;s leased facilities comprise an aggregate of
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage6"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	approximately 249,000 squ
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	are feet with leases that expire at various dates through December 2021.&nbsp;&nbsp;Faneuil believes the facilities under lease will be adequate for at least the next 12&#160;months.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Backlog
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s&#160;backlog&#160;represents executed contracts for future services.&nbsp;&nbsp;The majority of Faneuil&#8217;s contracts are long-term and obligate Faneuil to provide services over multiple years.&nbsp;&nbsp;Faneuil&#8217;s&#160;backlog&#160;may not represent guarantees of services as some of our contracts, especially with government entities, allow for cancellation under certain instances.&nbsp;&nbsp;Faneuil adjusts backlog to reflect contract cancellations, deferrals and revisions known at the reporting date; however, future contract modifications or cancellations may increase or reduce backlog and future revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following table reflects the amount of Faneuil&#8217;s contract&#160;backlog by the fiscal year we expect to recognize revenue (
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in millions
</FONT>
	):
</P>

	The majority of the decrease as of September 30, 2015 compared to September 30, 2016 was a result of revenue recognized during the year ended September 30, 2016 from contracts included in Faneuil&#8217;s backlog at September 30, 2015.

	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	See &#8220;Part I, Item 1A. Risk Factors - Risks Related to our Business Generally and our Common Stock -
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We may not receive the full amounts estimated under the contracts in our backlog, which could reduce our revenue in future periods below the levels anticipated. This makes backlog an uncertain indicator of future operating results.
</FONT>
	&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Seasonality
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil experiences seasonality within its various lines of business. For example, during the end of the calendar year through the end of the first calendar quarter, Faneuil generally experiences higher revenues with its healthcare customers as the customer contact centers increase operations during the enrollment periods of the healthcare exchanges. Faneuil&#8217;s revenue from its healthcare customers generally decreases during the remaining portion of the year after the enrollment period. Seasonality is less prevalent in the transportation industry though there is typically an increase in volume during the summer months.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Governmental Regulation
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil&#8217;s business is subject to many legal and regulatory requirements in the United States, covering such matters as data privacy, consumer protection, health care requirements, labor relations, taxation, internal and disclosure control obligations, governmental affairs and immigration. For example, Faneuil is subject to state and federal laws and regulations regarding the protection of consumer information commonly referred to as &#8220;non-public personal information.&#8221; For instance, the collection of patient data through Faneuil&#8217;s contact center services and medical device tracking services is subject to the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996, commonly known as HIPAA, which protects the privacy of patient data. These laws, regulations and agreements require Faneuil to develop and implement policies to protect non-public personal information and to disclose these policies to consumers before a customer relationship is established and periodically after that. These laws, regulations, and agreements limit Faneuil&#8217;s ability to use or disclose non-public personal information for other than the purposes originally intended. Many of these regulations, including those related to data privacy, are frequently changing and sometimes conflict with existing ones amongst the various jurisdictions in which Faneuil provides services. Violations of these laws and regulations could result in liability for damages, fines, criminal prosecution, unfavorable publicity and restrictions on Faneuil&#8217;s ability to operate. Faneuil&#8217;s failure to adhere to or successfully implement processes in response to changing regulatory requirements in this area could result in legal liability or impairment to Faneuil&#8217;s reputation in the marketplace, which could have a material adverse effect on Faneuil&#8217;s business, results of operations and financial condition. Also, because a substantial portion of Faneuil&#8217;s operating costs consists of labor costs, changes in governmental regulations relating to wages, healthcare and healthcare reform and other benefits or employment taxes could have a material adverse effect on Faneuil&#8217;s business, results of operations or financial condition.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage7"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU7">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Management
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Faneuil is led by ALJ board member Anna Van Buren, who has served as Faneuil&#8217;s President and Chief Executive Officer since 2009, and previously served in executive roles at Faneuil since 2004. For additional information regarding Ms.&#160;Van Buren, see &#8220;Part III, Item 10. Directors, Executive Officers and Corporate Governance.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets N&#8217; More
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Background
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets was originally organized in Nevada in 2007. We acquired Carpets from Levine Leichtman in 2014 for aggregate consideration of $5.25&#160;million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets is one of the largest floor covering retailers in Las Vegas, Nevada, and a provider of multiple products for the commercial, retail and home builder markets, including flooring, countertops, cabinets, window coverings and garage/closet organizers. In addition to a stone and solid surface fabrication facility, Carpets has five retail locations in the Las Vegas area.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Products and Services
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Floor Coverings
</FONT>
	. Carpets provides various floor coverings to home builders, commercial and retail customers including carpet, hardwood, laminate, tile, ceramic, porcelain, natural stone, vinyl plank, vinyl tile, area rugs and specialty flooring including bamboo, leather, cork and large format tile.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Countertops and Surrounds
</FONT>
	. Carpets provides countertop and surrounds, primarily for bathrooms and kitchens, including natural stone, granite, ceramic, porcelain, solid surface, quartz and piedrafina.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cabinets and Other Products
</FONT>
	. Carpets provides kitchen, bathroom, and garage cabinets, closet and closet organizers; and window coverings including blinds, shutters, and shades.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Customers
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets sells to a variety of customers, including home owners and home builders as well as to owners and operators of commercial buildings. Carpets&#8217; home building customers include some of the largest home builders in the United States, along with local builders in and around Las Vegas, Nevada. Carpets&#8217; commercial customers include general contractors, real estate investment firms/funds and commercial entities such as casinos and other companies looking to improve their office space. Carpets&#8217; retail customers include the general public interested in making home improvements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets bids directly with home builders on residential developments and is awarded flooring, countertops and surrounds and/or cabinet contracts. These contracts involve installing the base level products in each of the residential homes within the awarded development and, when requested, providing upgraded materials and services to the base level products. Carpets also bids on commercial work and is awarded contracts generally on a fixed price basis. These projects generally involve high-rise condos, office buildings, tenant improvements, off-strip casinos and general contractors. Carpets&#8217; marketing activities include billboards, Internet search engine optimization, banner advertising, car wraps, affiliate websites and radio and television advertising.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	A small number of customers have historically accounted for a substantial portion of Carpets net revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;The percentages of Carpets net revenues derived from its significant customers for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015 were as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:2PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

	Less than 10% of Carpet net revenues.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Suppliers
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU8">
</A>
	Carpets has historically purchased materials from a small number of suppliers primarily to control the quality of the product and to capitalize on volume discounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;If these suppliers were unable to provide materials on a timely basis, Carpets management believes
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage8"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	alternative suppliers could provide the required materials with minimal disruption to the business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Historically, Carpets has never experienced any significant delay or shortage in the supply of materials.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The percentages of Carpets inventory purchases from its significant suppliers for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015 were as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

	Carpets&#8217; backlog represents multi-year contracts with contractors to build-out communities, which typically takes about two to three years.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following table reflects the amount of Carpets&#8217; contract&#160;backlog by the fiscal year we expect to recognize revenue (

	in millions

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The majority of the increase as of September 30, 2016 compared to September 30, 2015 was a result of new contracts executed during the year ended September 30, 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	See &#8220;Part I, Item 1A. Risk Factors - Risks Related to our Business Generally and our Common Stock -
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We may not receive the full amounts estimated under the contracts in our backlog, which could reduce our revenue in future periods below the levels anticipated. This makes backlog an uncertain indicator of future operating results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Competition
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets&#8217; primary competitors are other flooring, countertop and surround and cabinet providers in the Las Vegas area, such as Interior Specialist Inc. and Classic Flooring, as well as large box stores like Lowe&#8217;s, Home Depot and RC Willey. Carpets believes that its competitive advantages include a comprehensive and high-end quality solution for home builders for flooring, surrounds and cabinets, which provides them with a single point of accountability. Carpets also competes with discounted flooring companies like Cloud Carpet and Carpets Galore.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Seasonality
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets generally experiences seasonality within the home building business as the number of houses sold during the winter months is generally lower than other times during the year. Conversely, the number of houses sold and delivered during the remaining portion of the year increases in comparison.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employees
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets had 142 employees as of September&#160;30, 2016. None of its employees are subject to any collective bargaining agreements. Carpets considers its employee relations good.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage9"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU9">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Properties
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets leases and operates five retail locations and one fabrication facility in and around Las Vegas, NV.&nbsp;&nbsp;Carpets corporate offices are also located in Las Vegas, NV. Carpets leased facilities comprise an aggregate of approximately 118,000 square feet with leases that expire at various dates through September 2021. Carpets believes the facilities under lease will be adequate for at least the next 12&#160;months.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Management
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets is led by Steve Chesin, who has served as its Chief Executive Officer since 2007. For additional information about Mr.&#160;Chesin, see &#8220;Part III, Item 10. Directors, Executive Officers and Corporate Governance.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix Color Corp.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Background
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix was originally incorporated in New York in 1979 and reincorporated in Delaware in 1996. We acquired Phoenix from Visant Corporation in 2015 for aggregate consideration of $88.3&#160;million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix is a premier full-service, full-color printer with over 35 years of superior print experience. Drawing on a broad spectrum of materials and decorative technologies, Phoenix produces memorable, value-added components, heavily illustrated books and specialty commercial products. Book publishers generally design book components to enhance the sales appeal of their books. The production of book components requires specialized equipment, materials, and finishes and often demands high-quality, intricate work. As a result, many leading publishers rely on specialty printers such as Phoenix to supply high-quality book components. This same philosophy applies to labels, packaging, and specialty commercial products, where Phoenix&#8217;s customers require the knowledge and expertise of a printer that can enhance their products for sale into the commercial marketplace. Phoenix has been servicing the publishing industry within the United States since 1979 and has formed lasting relationships with many of the biggest names in book publishing.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	As a domestic manufacturer, Phoenix offers extensive, in-house digital pre-press capabilities and its technologically advanced UV printing platform supports an array of printing and finishing options. Phoenix&#8217;s innovative special effects include foil stamping, UV embellishments and laminations, as well as its trademarked products LithoFoil
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.5PT;">
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	&#174;
</SUP>
</FONT>
	, MetalTone&#8482;, Look of Leather&#8482; and VibraColor&#8482;.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Acquisition of Color Optics
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	On July 18, 2016, Phoenix acquired certain assets and assumed certain liabilities from AKI, Inc. (&#8220;AKI&#8221;) in respect of AKI&#8217;s Color Optics division (&#8220;Color Optics&#8221;) for an adjusted purchase price of $6.6 million cash.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Color Optics is a leading printing and packaging solutions business servicing the beauty, fragrance, cosmetic and consumer-packaged goods markets.&nbsp;&nbsp;The purchase of Color Optics complements Phoenix&#8217;s current product offerings and will allow Phoenix to expand and diversify its product offerings by leveraging its existing core competencies.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following is a summary of Color Optics revenue and earnings included in the Company&#8217;s consolidated statements of operations for the year ended&#160;September 30, 2016&#160;(
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	in thousands
</FONT>
	):
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(228
</P>

</EFX_INCOME_STATEMENT>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Products and Services
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Books and Components
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix offers several products for books and components, which represents over 90% of Phoenix net revenue.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix is a leader in providing distinctive cover components and high-quality, heavily illustrated and multi-colored books for all markets. With its technologically advanced prepress and press operations as well as an array of finishing applications and innovative special effects, Phoenix is committed to producing memorable, value-added products.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	6
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage10"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU10">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Labels and Packaging
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In recent years, Phoenix has expanded into the label and packaging markets to leverage its unique printing and finishing capabilities as well as its trademarked special effects and extensive offerings of finishes and coatings. In 2014, Phoenix acquired the Brady Palmer Company, establishing its presence in the cut and stack label market.&nbsp;&nbsp;With the purchase of Color Optics, Phoenix strengthened its presence in the label and packaging markets.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phoenix is continuing to pursue growth in the folding carton and box wrap markets as well, and has invested in additional manufacturing capabilities and sales and marketing personnel to support these efforts.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employees
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix had 391 employees as of September&#160;30, 2016, of which 12 are subject to a collective bargaining agreement. Phoenix considers its employee relations good.
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_7"></A>

	Customers

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Suppliers
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix has historically purchased raw materials from a small number of suppliers primarily to control the quality of the product and to capitalize on volume discounts.&nbsp;&nbsp;If these suppliers were unable to provide materials on a timely basis, Phoenix management believes alternative suppliers could provide the required materials with minimal disruption to the business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Historically, Phoenix has never experienced any significant delay or shortage in the supply of materials.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The percentages of Phoenix inventory purchases from its significant suppliers for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015 were as follows
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Backlog
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix&#8217;s backlog represents executed contracts that contain minimum volume commitments over multiple years for future product deliveries. Phoenix includes only the minimum commitments as backlog. As Phoenix&#8217;s executed contracts mostly provide for minimum volume commitments rather than minimum revenue commitments, the actual revenue from such contracts may differ from our backlog estimates as total order volume from Phoenix&#8217;s customers may vary. Phoenix adjusts backlog to reflect estimated order volumes delivered by its customers based on historical experience known at the reporting date; however, future&nbsp;&nbsp;variations in order volumes by Phoenix&#8217;s customers may increase or decrease backlog and future revenue.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	7
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:1PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The majority of the increase as of September 30, 2016 compared to September 30, 2015 was a result of new contracts with volume commitments executed during the year ended September 30, 2016 slightly offset by revenue recognized during the year ended September 30, 2016 from Phoenix&#8217;s backlog at September 30, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	See &#8220;Part I, Item 1A. Risk Factors - Risks Related to our Business Generally and our Common Stock -
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	We may not receive the full amounts estimated under the contracts in our backlog, which could reduce our revenue in future periods below the levels anticipated. This makes backlog an uncertain indicator of future operating results.
</FONT>
	&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Seasonality
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	There is seasonality to Phoenix&#8217;s business. Education book component sales (school and college) traditionally peak in the first and second quarters of the calendar year. Other book components sales traditionally peak in the third quarter of the calendar year. Book sales also traditionally peak in the third quarter of the calendar year. The fourth quarter of the calendar year traditionally has been Phoenix&#8217;s weakest quarter. These seasonal factors are not significant.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Competition
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The printing industry in general, and the printing and manufacturing of books in particular, is extremely competitive. Over the past several years, there has been significant consolidation in the publishing industry, such that fewer publishers control a greater share of the market. Although there are still many small, independent publishers, they do not wield the leverage held by major publishing houses. Additionally, the printing industry has experienced a reduction in demand for trade books due to the impact of the e-book market and a reduction in textbooks due to lower state government funding, alternative product formats and digital distribution of content.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix&#8217;s primary competitors in the printing and manufacturing of books and book components include, but are not limited to, LSC Communications, Coral Graphics, Quad Graphics and Worzalla. There is no reliable industry data available to determine Phoenix&#8217;s market share and position versus that of its competitors. With respect to book components, a portion of the products is produced by the book manufacturers and a portion by component printers. The dollar value of book components manufactured by the book manufacturers or by other component printers is unknown. Phoenix and Coral Graphics are the two primary trade book component manufacturers used by major publishers in the U.S. market. Most high-quality, heavily-illustrated and multi-colored books sold in the U.S. are produced outside of the U.S. Phoenix competes with Worzalla and several domestic book manufacturers for that portion that is produced domestically.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Properties
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix owns its principal properties for corporate offices and production located in Hagerstown, MD. Phoenix&#8217;s owned facilities comprise an aggregate of approximately 276,000 square feet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Color Optics leases approximately 84,000 square feet in Rockaway, NJ.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease expires in 2020.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phoenix believes its facilities will be adequate for at least the next 12&#160;months.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Management
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix is led by our board member Marc Reisch, who serves as its Chairman and previously served as its Chief Executive Officer from 2008 to 2015. For additional information regarding Mr.&#160;Reisch, see &#8220;Part III, Item 10. Directors, Executive Officers and Corporate Governance.&#8221;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	8

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Additional Information About ALJ and its Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ was originally incorporated in the State of Delaware under the name Nuparent, Inc. on June&#160;22, 1999. The Company&#8217;s name was changed to YouthStream Media Networks, Inc. on June&#160;24, 1999, and that name was used through October&#160;23, 2006. The Company&#8217;s name was changed to ALJ Regional Holdings, Inc. on October&#160;23, 2006.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	As of September&#160;30, 2016, ALJ had two employees, its Executive Chairman and its Chief Financial Officer, performing services dedicated primarily to general corporate and administrative matters. Neither employee is represented by a labor union.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Intellectual Property
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We rely on copyright, trademark, and trade secret laws as well as contractual restrictions to protect our proprietary information and intellectual property rights. We control access to our proprietary information and intellectual property, in part, by entering into confidentiality and invention assignment agreements with our employees, contractors, and business partners. We also control the use of our proprietary information and intellectual property through provisions in our client agreements and distribution partner agreements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We have seven registered trademarks and one registered copyright in the United States as well as a number of common law trademarks and trade names. We rely substantially on unpatented proprietary technology. We do not consider the success of our business, as a whole, to be dependent on our intellectual property.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
