<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU42">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Robert Scott Fritz
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Mr.&#160;Fritz has served as a director since January 2003. Since May&#160;1982, Mr.&#160;Fritz has served as the President of Robert Fritz and Sons Sales Compan
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	y, a New Jersey-based food broker and paper distributor that he owns.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&#160;Fritz earned a B.S. in Business from Fairleigh Dickinson University.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Rae Ravich
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Ms.&#160;Ravich has served as a director since June 2014. Ms.&#160;Ravich is an Associate in the direct lending group at TCW Financial Planning LLC. Previously, Ms.&#160;Ravich was a Financial Analyst at Houlihan Lokey, which she joined in July&#160;2013. Ms.&#160;Ravich has dual B.S. degrees from the Wharton School and the Nursing School at the University of Pennsylvania. Ms.&#160;Ravich is the daughter of Jess Ravich, ALJ&#8217;s Executive Chairman.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	John Scheel
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Mr.&#160;Scheel has served as a director since September&#160;2006. From August&#160;2006 to February 2013, Mr.&#160;Scheel was the President and Chief Executive Officer of the Company. Mr.&#160;Scheel is a principal of, and also currently serves as the Chief Operating Officer of Pinnacle Steel.&nbsp;&nbsp;He served as the plant manager for the Company&#8217;s former subsidiary Kentucky Electric Steel&#8217;s (&#8220;KES&#8221;) steel mini-mill in Ashland, Kentucky (the &#8220;Mill&#8221;) and managed the operations of KES on our behalf from January&#160;2004 until its sale in February&#160;2013. Following such sale, Mr.&#160;Scheel not only continued to manage the Mill for Optima as its general manager, but also managed the melt shop and caster for Warren Steel Holdings EAF in Warren, Ohio, which is also managed by Optima. Prior to joining Pinnacle, Mr.&#160;Scheel held various positions of increased responsibility at AK Steel, Nucor Corporation and Birmingham Steel Management. Mr.&#160;Scheel holds both B.S. and M.S. degrees in Metallurgical Engineering from Purdue University and a Master of Business Administration in Finance and International Business from Xavier University.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Anna Van Buren
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Ms.&#160;Van Buren has served as a director since November&#160;2013. Ms.&#160;Van Buren was appointed President and Chief Executive Officer of Faneuil, in April&#160;2009, after previously serving as President and Chief Operating Officer from 2007 to 2009, as Vice President and Managing Director of Faneuil&#8217;s Government Services Division from 2005 to 2007, and as Vice President of Business Development from 2004 to 2005. Prior to her association with Faneuil, Ms.&#160;Van Buren founded Capital Initiatives, a consulting service for clients seeking visibility among federal lawmakers with the objective of encouraging legislative action, and operated numerous government services and marketing companies. Ms.&#160;Van Buren has served in leadership roles for many civic and business organizations including chairmanship of the United Way of the Virginia Peninsula, the Peninsula Chamber of Commerce and the NASA Aeronautics Support Team. She is the recipient of numerous awards including the Women in Business Achievement Award by Inside Business Magazine, the Presidential Citizenship Award from Hampton University and the NCCJ Humanitarian Award. Ms.&#160;Van Buren holds a degree from Hollins University and the University of Virginia Executive School.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Michael Borofsky
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Mr.&#160;Borofsky has served as a director since September 2013. Since 2003, Mr.&#160;Borofsky has been Senior Vice President of MacAndrews&#160;&amp; Forbes. Prior to that, Mr.&#160;Borofsky worked for Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher&#160;&amp; Flom LLP, where he specialized in mergers&#160;&amp; acquisitions, and was an analyst at Goldman Sachs. Mr.&#160;Borofsky earned a B.A. from Yale University and a J.D. from Columbia University School of Law.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Marc Reisch
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Mr.&#160;Reisch was appointed Chairman of Phoenix in August&#160;2015 and has served as a director of the Company since that time. Mr.&#160;Reisch served as Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President of Visant and Visant Holding Corp. from October&#160;2004 to November&#160;2015. Prior to joining Visant, he served as Senior Advisor to Kohlberg Kravis Roberts&#160;&amp; Co. and has over 35 years of experience in the printing and publishing industries. Mr.&#160;Reisch holds a Bachelor of Science Degree and a Master of Business Administration degree from Cornell University.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Margarita Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Ms.&#160;Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez has served as a director since November 2015. Ms.&#160;Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez is a Principal and Founding Partner of Hern&#225;ndez Ventures, a privately held entity engaged in the acquisition and management of a variety of business interests. She has served in this capacity since 1988. Prior to founding Hern&#225;ndez Ventures, Ms.&#160;Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez was an attorney with the law firm of McCutcheon, Black, Verleger&#160;&amp; Shea, where she focused on domestic and international business and real estate transactions. Ms.&#160;Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez has a B.A. from University of San Diego and a J.D. from UCLA School of Law.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Key Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Steve Chesin
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	. Mr.&#160;Chesin has served as the Chief Executive Officer of Carpets since August&#160;2007. From 2002 to 2007, Mr.&#160;Chesin served as the Executive Vice President of Carpets. From 1995 to 2001, Mr.&#160;Chesin served as the Senior Vice President and the Chief Operating Officer of Carpet Barn Inc., a subsidiary of Nations Flooring Inc. Mr.&#160;Chesin attended University of Nevada, Las Vegas.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Involvement in Certain Legal Proceedings
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	To the best of our knowledge, none of our directors or officers has appeared as a party during the past ten years in any legal proceedings that may bear on his ability or integrity to serve as a director or officer of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	39
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage43"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU43">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Section&#160;16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Section 16(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 requires our directors and executive officers, as well as persons who own more than 10% of a registered class of our equity securities, to file with the SEC initial reports of ownership and reports of changes in beneficial ownership. Directors, executive officers, and greater than 10% shareholders are required by SEC regulations to furnish us with copies of all Section 16(a) forms they file. Based solely upon a review of copies of Section 16(a) reports and representations received by us from reporting persons, and without conducting any independent investigation of our own, we believe all Forms 3, 4 and 5 were timely filed with the SEC by such reporting persons during the year ended September 30, 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Code of Business Conduct and Ethics
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our Board of Directors adopted a Code of Business Conduct and Ethics (&#8220;Code&#8221;), which is applicable to all employees of ALJ, ALJ subsidiaries, and members of our Board of Directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Code addresses, among other things, honesty and ethical conduct, conflicts of interest, compliance with laws and regulations, policies related to disclosure requirements under federal securities laws, confidentiality, trading on insider information, and reporting violations under the Code.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any amendment of our Code, or waiver thereof, applicable to our principal executive officer, principal financial officer, directors, or persons performing similar functions will be disclosed on our website within five days of the date of such amendment or waiver. In the case of a waiver, the nature of the waiver, the name of the person to whom the waiver was granted and the date of the waiver will also be disclosed.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our Code can be found in the Investor Relations section of the Company&#8217;s website,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	www.aljregionalholdings.com
</FONT>
	, and is attached to this Form 10-K as Exhibit 14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, a printed copy of our Code can be requested by writing our Chief Financial Officer at 244 Madison Avenue, PMB #358, New York, NY 10016.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Committees of the Board of Directors
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Board of Directors has a standing audit committee (&#8220;Audit Committee&#8221;) and compensation, nominating, and corporate governance committee (&#8220;Compensation, Nominating, and Corporate Governance Committee&#8221;). The composition and responsibilities of each committee are described below. Members will serve on these committees until their resignation or until otherwise determined by the Board of Directors.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Board of Directors has determined that all members of both committees are independent under the applicable rules and regulations of NASDAQ and the SEC as currently in effect.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee and the Compensation, Nominating, and Corporate Governance Committee each operate under a written charter approved by the Board of Directors. Each committee will review and reassess the adequacy of its charter periodically. The charters of both committees are available in the Investor Relations section of the Company&#8217;s website,&#160;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	www.aljregionalholdings.com
</FONT>
	.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following chart details the current membership of each committee:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	Our Audit Committee consists of Messrs. Scheel, Borofsky and Fritz, with Mr.&#160;Scheel chairing this committee. All members of our Audit Committee are independent directors and meet the requirements for financial literacy as defined by SEC guidelines. Our Board of Directors has determined that Mr.&#160;Scheel is an &#8220;audit committee financial expert&#8221; as defined by SEC guidelines.&nbsp;&nbsp;

<EFX_COMPENSATION>
<A NAME="FIS_COMPENSATION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU45">
</A>
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_11_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_11_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION">
</A>
	ITEM 11. EXECUTI
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	VE COMPENSATION
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Summary Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our executive compensation program, consists of a three-part compensation strategy that includes base salary, annual discretionary cash bonuses and equity incentive compensation, is designed to (i)&#160;pay for performance to encourage both Company and individual achievement; (ii)&#160;encourage efficient use of shareholder resources; and (iii)&#160;provide market competitive compensation to attract and retain highly qualified individuals who are capable of making significant contributions to the long-term success of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We do not adopt express formulae for weighting different elements of compensation or for allocating between long-term and short-term compensation but strive to develop comprehensive packages that are competitive with those offered by other companies with which we compete to attract and retain talented executives. Under our compensation practices, cash compensation consists of an annual base salary and discretionary bonuses.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity-based compensation is primarily stock options and restricted stock awards.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following table sets forth, for the years indicated, all compensation awarded to, paid to or earned by each of our named executive officers and certain other key employees.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employment Arrangements with Named Executive Officers and Other Key Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Named Executive Officers
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Jess Ravich.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	Mr.&#160;Ravich has served as our Executive Chairman since February&#160;2013.&nbsp;&nbsp;In December&#160;2015, the Board of Directors reviewed and reconsidered the compensation for our Executive Chairman and approved an executive chairman compensation package comprised of (i)&#160;an annual retainer of $125,000 in cash and (ii)&#160;an annual grant of restricted stock units with a value of $100,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;Following the adoption of this policy, Mr.&#160;Ravich will only receive compensation as our Executive Chairman and will no longer receive additional compensation for his services as our director.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	During the year ended September 30, 2016, Mr. Ravich received $125,000 in compensation and 21,645 shares of restricted common stock valued at $100,000, as compensation for his services as our Executive Chairman.&nbsp;&nbsp;During the year ended September&#160;30, 2015, Mr.&#160;Ravich received $125,000 in compensation for his services as our Executive Chairman and options to purchase 350,000 shares of our common stock at a price of $4.00 per share, which were fully vested upon grant and expire on August&#160;3, 2022, as compensation for the additional services that he performed in connection with our acquisition of Phoenix.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Ravich received $35,000 as director compensation for the year ended September 30, 2015, of which all was paid in cash.
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Anna Van Buren.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	During October&#160;2013, concurrent with ALJ&#8217;s acquisition of Faneuil, Faneuil entered into an employment agreement with Ms.&#160;Van Buren through December&#160;31, 2018. Pursuant to her employment agreement, Ms.&#160;Van Buren receives an annual salary of $520,000 and is eligible to earn an annual bonus equal to ten percent (10%) of Faneuil&#8217;s defined EBITDA, before any bonus amount owed to Ms.&#160;Van Buren, in excess of $5,000,000. If Ms.&#160;Van Buren&#8217;s employment is terminated without cause or by Ms.&#160;Van Buren for good reason, Ms.&#160;Van Buren will be eligible to receive: (i)&#160;her base salary for the greater of one year or one-half of the remaining term of the employment agreement, and (ii)&#160;the full annual bonus for the year in which such termination occurs if Ms.&#160;Van Buren would have been otherwise entitled to the bonus for such year had she still been employed when such bonus would have been paid.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Marc Reisch.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	August 2015, concurrent with ALJ&#8217;s acquisition of Phoenix, ALJ entered into an employment agreement with Mr.&#160;Reisch through December&#160;31, 2018. Pursuant to his employment agreement, Mr.&#160;Reisch receives an annual salary of $200,000 and is eligible to earn an annual bonus equal to five percent (5%)&#160;of the defined EBITDA of Phoenix in excess of $20,000,000, before any bonus amount owed to Mr.&#160;Reisch and the Chief Operating Officer of Phoenix.&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with ALJ&#8217;s acquisition of Phoenix, ALJ granted Mr. Reisch an option to purchase 250,000 shares of ALJ&#8217;s common stock at $4.27 per share.&nbsp;&nbsp;The option expires on August&#160;13, 2025. If Mr.&#160;Reisch&#8217;s employment is terminated without cause or by Mr.&#160;Reisch for good reason, Mr.&#160;Reisch will be eligible to receive (i): his&#160;base salary for the greater of one year or one-half of the remaining term of the employment agreement, (ii)&#160;the full annual bonus for the year in which such termination occurs, if Mr.&#160;Reisch would have been otherwise entitled to a bonus for such year had he still been employed, and (iii)&#160;the full annual bonus for the year prior to the year in which Mr.&#160;Reisch is so terminated, if at the time of termination Mr.&#160;Reisch has otherwise earned a full annual bonus for such prior year and has not yet been paid such bonus due to such termination.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Other Key Employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	T.&#160;Robert Christ.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	Mr. Christ has served as our Chief Financial Officer since July 2008.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	For the year ended September 30, 2016 and for the nine months ended September&#160;30, 2015, Mr.&#160;Christ received a salary of $17,500 per month from ALJ and its subsidiaries. For the three months ended December&#160;31, 2014, Mr.&#160;Christ received a salary of $15,000 per month from ALJ and its subsidiaries. During the year ended September&#160;30, 2015, Mr.&#160;Christ received options to purchase 50,000 shares of common stock at a price of $4.00 per share, which were fully vested upon issuance and will expire on August&#160;3, 2022.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Christ received a $25,000 bonus for both the year ended September 30, 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Steve Chesin.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;COLOR:#000000;">
	April 2014, concurrent with ALJ&#8217;s acquisition of Carpets, Carpets entered into an employment agreement with Mr.&#160;Chesin through December&#160;31, 2017. Pursuant to his employment agreement, Mr.&#160;Chesin receives an annual salary of $300,000 and is eligible to earn an annual bonus at the discretion of the Board of Directors of Carpets.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Mr.&#160;Chesin&#8217;s employment is terminated without cause or by Mr.&#160;Chesin for good reason, Mr.&#160;Chesin will be eligible to receive his base salary for the greater of (i)&#160;one-half of the remaining term of the employment agreement, or (ii)&#160;six months plus an additional $3,000 per month for each month in the six-month period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	43

	In December&#160;2015, the Board of Directors reviewed and considered our outside director compensation and approved an outside director compensation package comprised of (i)&#160;an annual retainer of $40,000 in cash, (ii)&#160;an annual grant of restricted stock units with a value of $40,000, (iii)&#160;an additional $12,500 for the chair and $5,000 for each other member of the Audit Committee, and (iv)&#160;an additional $10,000 for the chair and $4,000 for each other member of the Compensation, Nominating, and Corporate Governance Committee.

<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_12_SECURITY_OWNERSHIP_CERTAIN_BENEF">
</A>
	ITEM 12. SECURITY OWNERSHIP OF CERTAIN BENEFICIAL OWNERS AND MANAGEMENT AND RELATED STOCKHOLDER MATTERS
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following table sets forth, as of November 30, 2016, information regarding the beneficial ownership of our common stock based upon the most recent information available to us for: (i) each person known by us to own beneficially more than five (5%) percent of our outstanding common stock, (ii) each of our named executive officers, directors, and other key employees, and (iii) all of our named executive officers, directors, and other key employees as a group.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless otherwise indicated, each of the persons listed below has sole voting and investment power with respect to the shares beneficially owned by them.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of November 30, 2016 there were 34,574,641
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
</FONT>
	shares of our common stock outstanding, which was the only class of voting securities outstanding.

	Includes 350,000 shares of common stock issuable upon the exercise of options that are either vested or will vest within 60 days from the date hereof.

<EFX_OFFICER_TRANSACTIONS>
<A NAME="FIS_OFFICER_TRANSACTIONS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU50">
</A>
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_13_CERTAIN_RELATIONSHIPS_RELATED_TR">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_ITEM_13_CERTAIN_RELATIONSHIPS_RELATED_TR">
</A>
	ITEM 13. CERTAIN RELATIONSHIPS RELATED T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	RANSACTIONS, AND DIRECTOR INDEPENDENCE.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Certain Relationships and Related Transactions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	During the year ended September 30, 2016, we entered into the following transaction required to be reported under Item 404 of Regulation S-K (&#8220;Item 404&#8221;):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Harland Clarke Holdings Corp. (&#8220;Harland Clarke&#8221;), a stockholder who owns ALJ shares in excess of five percent, is a counterparty to Faneuil in two contracts. One contract provides call center services to support Harland Clarke&#8217;s banking-related products and renews annual every April. The other contract provides managed print services and concludes September 30, 2018. Faneuil recognized revenue from Harland Clarke totaling $1,331,000 and $2,567,000 for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015, respectively. The associated cost of revenue was $1,268,000 and $2,432,000 for the years ended September 30, 2016 and 2015, respectively. All revenue from Harland Clarke contained similar terms and conditions as for other transactions of this nature entered into by ALJ.&nbsp;&nbsp;Total accounts receivable from Harland Clarke was $176,000 and $368,000 at September 30, 2016 and 2015, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	On April 21, 2016, the Company entered into a Trade Procedures Letter Agreement, pursuant to which IsZo Capital Management LP (&#8220;IsZo&#8221;), a stockholder who owned in excess of 5% of ALJ shares, sold an aggregate of 2,000,000 shares of the Company to the Company, Jess Ravich, Marc Reisch, John Scheel and Margarita Palau Hernandez, each a director of the Company, and certain other parties (the &#8220;IsZo Sale&#8221;). Pursuant to the IsZo Sale, IsZo received gross proceeds of $7,780,000, the Company repurchased 500,000 shares for an aggregate consideration of $1,945,000, Mr. Ravich acquired 350,000 shares for an aggregate consideration of $1,361,500, Mr. Reisch acquired 100,000 shares for an aggregate consideration of $389,000, Mr. Scheel acquired 50,000 shares for an aggregate consideration of $194,500 and Ms. Pal&#225;u Hern&#225;ndez acquired 50,000 shares for an aggregate consideration of $194,500.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Director Independence
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The following directors qualify as &#8220;independent&#8221; in accordance with the rules and regulations of the SEC and NASDAQ as applicable:
</P>

	ITEM 14. PRINCIPAL ACCOUNTING FEES AND SERVICES.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our Audit Committee engaged Mayer Hoffman McCann P.C. (&#8220;MHM&#8221;) to serve as our independent registered public accounting firm for the year ending September 30, 2016. The selection of MHM was approved by our shareholders at the 2016 annual meeting of shareholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Mayer Hoffman McCann P.C. leases substantially all its personnel, who work under the control of MHM shareholders, from wholly-owned subsidiaries of CBIZ, Inc., including CBIZ MHM, LLC, in an alternative practice structure.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Pre-Approval Policies and Procedures
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Consistent with policies of the SEC regarding auditor independence and the Audit Committee Charter, the Audit Committee has the responsibility for appointing, setting compensation and overseeing the work of the registered independent public accounting firm (the &#8220;Firm&#8221;).&#160;The Audit Committee&#8217;s policy is to pre-approve all audit and permissible non-audit services provided by the Firm.&#160;Pre-approval is detailed as to the particular service to category of services and is generally subject to a specific budget.&#160;The Audit Committee may also pre-approve particular services on a case-by-case basis.&#160;In assessing request for services by the Firm, the Audit Committee considers whether such services are consistent with the Firm&#8217;s independence, whether the Firm is likely to provide the
<FONT STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;COLOR:#000000;">
	most effective and efficient service based upon their familiarity with the Company, and whether the service could enhance the Company&#8217;s ability to manage or control risk or improve audit quality.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	All of the services relating to the fees described in the table above were approved by the
</FONT>
	Audit Committee
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;

	48

<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	POWER OF ATTORNEY
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	KNOW ALL PERSONS BY THESE PRESENTS, that each person whose signature appears below constitutes and appoints Jess Ravich and T. Robert Christ, and each of them, as his true and lawful attorneys-in-fact and agents, with full power of substitution and resubstitution, for her or him and in her or his name, place, and stead, in any and all capacities, to sign any and all amendments to this Annual Report on Form 10-K, and to file the same, with all exhibits thereto, and other documents in connection therewith, with the Securities and Exchange Commission, granting unto said attorneys-in-fact and agents, and each of them, full power and authority to do and perform each and every act and thing requisite and necessary to be done in connection therewith, as fully to all intents and purposes as she or he might or could do in person, hereby ratifying and confirming that all said attorneys-in-fact and agents, or any of them or their or his substitute or substitutes, may lawfully do or cause to be done by virtue hereof.

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM_REPORT_OF_INDEPENDENT_ACCNT_FIRM">
</A>
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU58">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	To the Board of Directors and Stockholders of
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ Regional Holdings, Inc.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We have audited the accompanying consolidated balance sheets of
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ALJ Regional Holdings, Inc. and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
	(the &#8220;Company&#8221;) as of September 30, 2016 and 2015, and the related consolidated statements of income, stockholders' equity, and cash flows for each of the two years in the period ended September 30, 2016.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Our audits also included the financial statement schedule listed in the Index at Item&#160;15.
</FONT>
	These financial statements and schedule are the responsibility of the Company&#8217;s management.&#160; Our responsibility is to express an opinion on these financial statements and schedule based on our audits.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We conducted our audits in accordance with the standards of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&#160; Those standards require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about whether the financial statements are free of material misstatement.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	The Company is not required to have, nor were we engaged to perform, an audit of its internal control over financial reporting.&#160; Our audits included consideration of internal control over financial reporting as a basis for designing audit procedures that are appropriate in the circumstances, but not for the purpose of expressing an opinion on the effectiveness of
</FONT>
	the Company&#8217;s
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	internal control over financial reporting.&#160; Accordingly, we express no such opinion.&#160;
</FONT>
	An audit includes examining, on a test basis, evidence supporting the amounts and disclosures in the financial statements.&#160; An audit also includes assessing the accounting principles used and significant estimates made by management, as well as evaluating the overall financial statement presentation.&#160; We believe that our audits provide a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In our opinion, the financial statements referred to above present fairly, in all material respects, the consolidated financial position of the Company as of September 30, 2016 and 2015, and the consolidated results of its operations and its cash flows for each of the two years in the period ended September 30, 2016, in conformity with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.&#160;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Also, in our opinion, the related financial statement schedule, when considered in relation to the basic financial statements taken as a whole, presents fairly in all material respects the information set forth therein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	/s/ Mayer Hoffman McCann P.C.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	San Diego, California
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0.37%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	December 22, 2016

	YEARS ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2016 AND 2015

	1. ORGANIZATION AND BASIS OF PRESENTATION
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Organization
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ Regional Holdings, Inc. (including subsidiaries, referred to collectively in this Report as &#8220;ALJ,&#8221;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;Company,&#8221; &#8220;our,&#8221; and &#8220;we&#8221;) is a holding company.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ&#8217;s primary assets as of September&#160;30, 2016, were all of the outstanding capital stock of the following companies:
</P>

Faneuil is headquartered in Hampton, Virginia.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ acquired Faneuil effective October&#160;19, 2013.

	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:2PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ has organized its business and corporate structure along the following business segments: Faneuil, Carpets, and Phoenix. ALJ is reported as corporate overhead.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Basis of Presentation
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The accompanying consolidated financial statements were prepared in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles in the United States of America (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;) and include the accounts of ALJ and subsidiaries.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	All intercompany items and transactions have been eliminated
</FONT>
	in consolidation.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ has reclassified certain prior period amounts to conform to current period presentation
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:ARIAL;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Such reclassifications had no impact on previously reported net income or cash flows.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2. SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Use of Estimates
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The preparation of the financial statements in conformity with GAAP requires management to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities, disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date of the financial statements, and the reported amounts of revenues and expenses during the reporting periods. Although actual results could differ materially from those estimates, such estimates are based on the best information available to management and management&#8217;s best judgments at the time. Significant estimates and assumptions by management are used for, but are not limited to, determining the fair value of assets and liabilities, including intangible assets acquired and allocation of acquisition purchase prices, estimated useful lives, recoverability of long-lived and intangible assets, the recoverability of goodwill, the realizability of deferred tax assets, stock-based compensation, the likelihood of material loss as a result of loss contingencies, customer lives, the allowance for doubtful accounts and inventory reserves, and calculation of insurance reserves.&nbsp;&nbsp;Actual results may differ materially from estimates.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Business Combinations
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Company&#160;accounts for business combinations&#160;under the acquisition method of accounting in accordance with the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#8220;FASB&#8221;) Accounting Standards Codification
</FONT>
	(&#8220;ASC&#8221;) 805, &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Business Combinations
</FONT>
	&#8221; (&#8220;ASC 805&#8221;).&#160;The Company&#160;recognizes the fair value of the assets acquired and liabilities assumed, immediately expenses transaction costs and accounts for restructuring plans separately from the business combination. The excess of the cost of the acquisition over the fair value of the net tangible and intangible assets acquired is recorded as goodwill. Results of operations of the acquired business are included in the consolidated statements of income from the effective date of acquisition.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	F-8
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage65"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU65">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	While ALJ uses its best estimates and assumptions to accurately value assets acquired and liabilities assumed at t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	he acquisition date, estimates are inherently uncertain and subject to refinement. As a result, during the measurement period, which may be up to one year from the acquisition date, ALJ records any adjustments to the assets acquired and liabilities assumed
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	with corresponding adjustments to goodwill. Upon the conclusion of the measurement period or final determination of the values of assets acquired or liabilities assumed, whichever comes first, any subsequent adjustments are recorded to the consolidated st
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	atements of income.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Cash and Cash Equivalents
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Cash and equivalents include all cash, demand deposits and money market accounts with original maturities of three months or less.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Accounts Receivable
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ presents accounts receivable, net of allowances for doubtful accounts and returns, to ensure accounts receivable are not overstated due to uncollectible accounts. Allowances, when required, are calculated based on a detailed review of certain individual customer accounts and an estimation of the overall economic conditions affecting ALJ&#8217;s customer base. ALJ reviews a customer&#8217;s credit history before extending credit. If the financial condition of its customers were to deteriorate, resulting in an impairment of their ability to make payments, additional allowances may be required.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Inventory
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Carpets.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	Inventory, which consists of carpet, wood, vinyl, granite and other related hard surfaces, cabinets and window treatments, is stated at the lower of cost or market.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cost is computed on a first-in, first-out basis (&#8220;FIFO&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Carpets reserves for slow-moving and obsolete inventory when management determines an item should be reserved based on historical and/or projected usage of the product.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obsolete or unsalable inventories are stated at net realizable value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Phoenix.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;">
	Inventory, which consists primarily of paper, laminating film and inks, is stated at lower of cost or market.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cost is determined using FIFO and includes direct materials, direct labor, and applicable overhead.&nbsp;&nbsp;Phoenix reserves for slow-moving and obsolete inventory when management determines an item should be reserved based on historical and/or projected usage of the product.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obsolete or unsalable inventories are stated at net realizable value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Assets Held for Sale
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Assets that ALJ intends to sell and are not used in current operations, are disclosed separately on the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Balance Sheet
</FONT>
	s and are valued at the lower of cost or realizable value.&nbsp;&nbsp;At September 30, 2016, ALJ owned an insignificant part of Bellator Sport Worldwide LLC (&#8220;Bellator&#8221;), and Phoenix owned equipment, which were both sold subsequent to year end.&nbsp;&nbsp;At September 30, 2015, Phoenix owned a building that was sold in January 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>

	Property and Equipment

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:2PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Property and equipment acquired in a business acquisition are recorded at fair value on the date of acquisition. Subsequent purchases are recorded at historical cost.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
</FONT>
	Significant improvements and betterments are capitalized. Routine repairs and maintenance are expensed when incurred. Gains and losses on disposal of fixed assets are recognized in the statements of income based on the net disposal proceeds less the carrying amount of the assets.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	F-9
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage66"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="ALJJ-10K_20160930_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU66">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Goodwill
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ALJ records goodwill when the purchase price of an acquisition exceeds the fair value of the net tangible and identified intangible assets acquired.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ assigns the goodwill to its reporting segments consistent with the expected fair value provided by the acquisition.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ performs an annual impairment assessment in the fourth quarter of each year, or more frequently if indicators of potential impairment exist, which includes evaluating qualitative and quantitative factors to assess the likelihood of an impairment of a segment&#8217;s goodwill.&nbsp;&nbsp;To date, ALJ has not recorded any goodwill impairment.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Intangible Assets
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	As of September 30, 2016 and 2015, all intangible assets were acquisition-related, recorded at fair value on the date acquired, and subject to amortization.&nbsp;&nbsp;ALJ amortizes intangible assets over their estimated useful life based on economic benefit using the straight-line method.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the quarter following the period in which the intangible asset becomes fully amortized, ALJ removes the fully amortized balances from the gross asset and accumulated amortization amounts.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The estimated useful life ranges for all identified intangible assets were as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP" BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:59.6%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Customer relationships
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#CFF0FC" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:36.42%;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	12-15
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:59.6%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Trade names
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:36.42%;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	15-30
</P>
</TD>
